RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S ME AGAIN bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced in the three path early, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, swung out to the four path to began a bid coming off the second turn and kicked clear in the final furlong. HEAVY WEIGHT raced in the two path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the far bend and chased the winner home in the lane. HIGHJUMP CHARLIE raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the four path and gained ground late. KALINBA bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, saved ground early, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and showed no kick. CORPORATE AFFAIR fought his rider a considerable amount while racing in the three path around the first turn, settled to duel on the inside up the backstretch, led briefly headed into the far turn, raced in the two path from there and faded in the stretch. RED JET bumped with the horses to either side and was forced to take up at the start, trailed the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCELLENT MARK raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, switched to the inside in upper stretch, gained ground while drifting in mildly and got up for the win late. ABE HONESTLY led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path coming around the bend and dueled down the lane, getting caught in the final strides. SIDNEY'S BID raced in the middle of the pack between horses early, navigated the turn from the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and kept on to the wire. DUN RIGHT chased the leaders on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the three path around the turn and weakened in the stretch. TEDDY'S HONOR raced off the pace up the backstretch, came around the bend in the two path and made no bid. R D BLESSING trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 84. Claiming Purse 18600. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Conditi on Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARRONADE raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the second turn, dueled in upper stretch and then drew off. NORTH CAROLINA led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far turn and in upper stretch, gave way with a furlong to go and chased the winner home from there. MAGICAL ADVENTURE raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and gained ground late. GENERAL COMMAND raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, navigated the far bend from the four path and finished evenly. MAGIC BOMB saved ground around the first bend, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and weakened in the lane. SKY TRAVELER raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. FORMAL TREASURE hit the gate leaving it, raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and made no bid. AMBUSHED trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turns and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY'N AWESOME stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, launched a bid in upper stretch and got up for the win late. DREAM CONCERT led the way up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and was caught in the final strides. BELMAR SUMMER raced off the pace early, navigated the turn from the four path and gained ground mildly in the stretch while never threatening the top two. PRINCESS CHESSIE chased the leader between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. DEVRA WARRIOR tracked the frontrunner on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and continued to fade from there. WISHIN N KISSIN trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 92. Claiming Purse 20500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered) (Condition E ligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXACTING led the field from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to show the way while saving ground around the far turn and held that margin to the wire. SAVVY LAYLA raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the three path, challenged the frontrunner passing the quarter pole and chased that rival home in the lane. WAR CROSS raced in the two path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and gained ground mildly in the stretch. MISTA DONZELLA raced inside in the middle of the pack through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far bend and finished evenly. CHESS'S DREAM saved ground early, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and weakened in the lane. MR. SARCASTIC raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace between horses, swung out to the five path for the run around the second bend and showed no kick. MARQUET MALICE raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the four path and was outkicked in the stretch. HOLD THE SPICE raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the five path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 95. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Clai ming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KING CAIRO stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the turn, began a bid passing the quarter pole, gained ground on the rail in upper stretch, kicked clear and held that margin to the wire. SAN COSTANTINO hopped up and bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path coming around the bend and gained ground late. OMATI led the way on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, dueled from the two path around the turn and chased on to the finish. UNFLAPPABLE MAX tracked the leaders between horses up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the turn and kept on to the finish. TONY SMALL bumped with the horse to his inside at the break, raced off the pace early, came around the turn in the three path and improved position in the lane while never threatening. SAVAGE chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and weakened from there. FIERCE WARRIOR raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the two path and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 7 1 1/16M Turf CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKLOW GAL was sent to an early lead while saving ground around the first turn, opened up on the field while racing up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and dug in in the stretch to hold the win. GLORIOUS WAVE raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and dueled to the wire but could not get by the winner. EMPTY ENVELOPE saved ground early, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far bend, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. ITRIEDSELLINGHER raced inside at the back of the pack through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. CAIRO WINNER saved ground early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, navigated the far bend from the three path and weakened in the lane. BANK BUSTER raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the four path and made no bid. EMPIRE GIRL raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn still in the two path and showed no kick. HOLY SKULL trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn, dropped back further racing up the backstretch and was eased through the final half mile, crossed the wire and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1M 40Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORD DARNLEY raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn, kicked clear while drifting out in upper stretch and drew off to the wire. LIVEFORTHESONG raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the pace setter between horses up the backstretch, came around the second bend still in the four path, was in tight quarters when LORD DARNLEY drifted out in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. HAD RIGHT trailed the field from the four path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the four path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position in the stretch. COMMANDER KEITH raced in the five path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the two path and improved position in the lane. EIGHT WEEKS LONG raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, came around the far turn in the five path and finished evenly. GRAND PLAYER saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend and weakened in the stretch. SWIFT KID saved ground around the first bend, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the five path and showed no kick. MUNDO MIX hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the six path around the first turn, opened up on the field coming up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and continued to tire in the lane. DON H raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and faded from there.

ENTRY.OWNER: GOP Racing Stable and Impact Thoroughbreds LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 86. Claiming Purse 17100. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE SKIPSTER saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch and around the far bend, dug in gamely in the stretch and battled to the wire to hold the win. SHIMMERING LEROID raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail coming around the second turn and dueled to the finish to narrowly miss. IN HONOR OF ARTIE raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. FAST PAYDAY raced in the two path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and gained ground mildly in the lane. KING OF CHAOS hopped up leaving the gate, trailed the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and improved position in the stretch. THE BEST DISTANCE raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn still in the two path and weakened from there. HEREBY raced in the two path early, came up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, challenged from the four path coming around the far turn and flattened out in the stretch. BATTLE CREEK saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. MIDNIGHT TEQUILA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far bend from the three path and tired in the lane. REBEL EMPIRE raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the far turn and tired quickly in the final furlong.
